info.name: Soho House API
info.description:
The Soho House API allows you to programmatically interact with various Soho House resources.

This API conforms to [JSON API](http://jsonapi.org/), if you are unfamiliar with JSONAPI, please
visit the website to get a sense of how this API is defined, and the rationale behind it.

**Note:** Some endpoints or properties within endpoints are not available, these will be marked with **NOT AVAILABLE** in their description

**Note:** Auth swagger moved, enter "./sso.yaml" in the expolore field to see it

The changelog for this swagger can be viewed [here](/changelog.html)

This API is best consumed with a JSON:API client:
- [js client](https://github.com/holidayextras/jsonapi-client)
- [ruby client](https://github.com/JsonApiClient/json_api_client)
- [python client](https://github.com/qvantel/jsonapi-client)

For more client libraries, see [Implementations](http://jsonapi.org/implementations/)
